place.name: CORNELLY
place.gazetteerText: CORNELLY, a parish in Truro district, Cornwall; 1¼ mile WNW of Tregony, and 2¾ SSW of Grampound Road r. station. Post town, Tregony, under Grampound, Cornwall. Acres, 1, 348. Real property, £1, 307. Pop., 99. Houses, 18. The property is divided among a few. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Exeter. Value, £47. Patron, the Vicar of Probus. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
